33:10.680 --> 33:12.614
(sighs)

33:19.830 --> 33:21.457
Hmm...

33:21.500 --> 33:23.798
That didn't solve anything.

33:23.830 --> 33:25.593
Weird, right?

33:25.630 --> 33:28.497
You know what else it
won't solve? Alistair.

33:28.540 --> 33:30.235
You know why he used
drugs last week?

33:30.270 --> 33:32.500
Because he was an addict,
just like you.

33:32.540 --> 33:34.371
I'm sorry he's gone,
but his relapsing

33:34.410 --> 33:36.628
doesn't change a thing for you;
not one single thing.

33:36.680 --> 33:40.070
You woke up today,
you didn't use drugs,
just like yesterday.

33:40.110 --> 33:41.646
You know what you
have to do tomorrow?

33:41.680 --> 33:43.648
Wake up and
not use drugs.

33:43.680 --> 33:45.784
That is just how it is;
that is how it's going to be.

33:45.820 --> 33:48.118
Thank you. Are you quite
finished telling me
things I already know?

33:48.160 --> 33:49.752
Are you ready to start
acting like you know them?

33:49.790 --> 33:51.621
I've decided I'm quite
ashamed of my behavior

33:51.660 --> 33:53.287
over the last few days,
all right?

33:53.330 --> 33:55.150
I took the passing
of a dear friend,

33:55.200 --> 33:57.498
_and I twisted it into
an indulgence in narCI55ism.

33:57.530 --> 33:59.566
It's left me in a mood.

34:00.800 --> 34:03.234
Alistair was a friend.

34:03.270 --> 34:04.828
One of only a handful.

34:04.870 --> 34:06.406
And-and-and...

34:06.440 --> 34:09.170
losing a member
of such a select group

34:09.210 --> 34:11.804
has felt quite...
substantial.

34:13.810 --> 34:17.348
My tantrum upset you,
and I apologize.

34:17.380 --> 34:19.245
Again.

34:19.290 --> 34:21.758
But I assure you,
I-I'm no closer to using

34:21.790 --> 34:25.783
than I was yesterday,
or the day before that
or the day before that.

34:27.660 --> 34:31.198
If I was, I would tell you.

34:32.200 --> 34:34.691
(phone dings)

34:34.740 --> 34:37.300
Is that the captain?
It's my mother.

34:37.340 --> 34:38.762
She just heard
about some lunatic

34:38.810 --> 34:41.301
trying to poison a bunch
of dairy cows with anthrax.

34:41.340 --> 34:43.433
She want us to throw away
all of our milk.

34:43.480 --> 34:44.777
WATSON:
So now we know.

34:44.810 --> 34:46.675
Hmm.

34:46.710 --> 34:47.870
Your mother's
not the only person

34:47.910 --> 34:50.276
succumbing
to anthrax hysteria.

34:50.320 --> 34:52.686
According to the news,
people all over the city

34:52.720 --> 34:54.585
are discarding
their dairy products,

34:54.620 --> 34:57.316
whether or not they originated
at the MacIntoshes' farm.

34:58.630 --> 34:59.858
Seriously?

34:59.890 --> 35:01.596
These expired a few days ago.

35:01.630 --> 35:03.598
Her text just reminded me.
You know what?

35:03.630 --> 35:05.359
I feel sorry
for that Bart MacIntosh.

35:05.400 --> 35:07.595
He said his farm
was already on the ropes

35:07.630 --> 35:09.689
and it wasn't doing well,
and now this.

35:09.740 --> 35:12.459
How unwell was it?

35:12.510 --> 35:14.137
He said the only thing
keeping it afloat

35:14.180 --> 35:15.829
was subsidies from
the government.

35:21.320 --> 35:24.141
Remind me to thank your mother
next time I see her, will you?

35:24.190 --> 35:25.214
For What?

35:26.220 --> 35:27.812
Well, we made an assumption

35:27.850 --> 35:29.681
when we realized
that the anthrax

35:29.720 --> 35:31.756
was in Eugene MacIntosh's
clutches.

35:31.790 --> 35:34.327
That he wanted to kill people.

35:34.360 --> 35:36.351
What if he didn't?

35:36.400 --> 35:39.892
What if he just wanted
to kill... cows?

35:44.610 --> 35:46.407
Go on ahead.
I'll catch up.

35:54.380 --> 35:56.519
Can I help you
with something, Captain?

35:56.550 --> 35:58.188
Yeah, actually,
my colleague here

35:58.220 --> 36:00.313
was hoping to ask you
a few questions

36:00.350 --> 36:02.352
about livestock insurance.

36:02.390 --> 36:04.483
Yes, your own,
specifically.

36:04.530 --> 36:06.919
We've learned that you have
exceedingly thorough coverage.

36:06.960 --> 36:09.394
Each one of your 1,342 cows

36:09.430 --> 36:11.523
is insured at full-market value?

36:11.570 --> 36:13.891
Yeah, they're the farm's
most valuable asset, so...

36:13.930 --> 36:15.795
$2,000 a head, right?

36:15.840 --> 36:17.398
Give or
take, yeah.

36:17.440 --> 36:19.499
So if your entire herd
were to be wiped out

36:19.540 --> 36:22.668
by some kind of a...
bovine holocaust,

36:22.710 --> 36:26.476
you'd receive $2.68 million,
give or take.

36:26.510 --> 36:28.944
You've enjoyed being
a farmer, Mr. MacIntosh?

36:28.980 --> 36:31.585
It's hard work, but...
I wouldn't change it, yeah.

36:31.620 --> 36:33.508
WATSON: Your father
actually willed the farm

36:33.550 --> 36:35.859
to you and your brother,
so you both stood to profit

36:35.890 --> 36:37.312
from the death
of the herd.

36:37.360 --> 36:38.827
No, wait a second.

36:38.860 --> 36:40.782
I-If you're trying to say
that Eugene was planning

36:40.830 --> 36:43.321
to poison the cattle
for the insurance._..
Actually, we're saying

36:43.360 --> 36:45.999
that you both planned
to poison the cattle.

36:46.030 --> 36:48.260
I told you What he said
the other night.

36:48.300 --> 36:50.268
I told you why
he did What he did.

36:50.300 --> 36:52.234
If we'd wanted
to make money off the cows,

36:52.270 --> 36:53.999
we just would've sold them.
Well, selling livestock

36:54.040 --> 36:56.372
is, of course, a quite
difficult process, isn't it?

36:56.410 --> 36:58.378
You've got inspections,
auctions, transport--

36:58.410 --> 37:01.573
all of these are expenses
which would cut deeply
into your payout.

37:01.620 --> 37:04.714
I mean, Wiping out the herd
in one go...

37:04.750 --> 37:06.889
far more cost-effective.

37:06.920 --> 37:07.739
WATSON: Of course,
that would require

37:07.790 --> 37:09.678
an _illness that
could Wipe them all out

37:09.720 --> 37:11.358
